Biography

William Cunningham Cunninghame Graham, 7th of Gartmore and 16th of Ardoch was born on 16 August 1775 at Gartmore, Perthshire, Scotland.

He was the son of Robert Cunninghame Graham, 6th of Gartmore and Anne Taylor.

He married, firstly, Anne Dickson, daughter of John Dickson, on 16 December 1798.

Children of Anne Dickson and William Cunningham Cunninghame Graham, 7th of Gartmore and 16th of Ardoch

1- Robert Cunningham Cunninghame Graham, 8th of Gartmore b. 14 Sep 1799, d. 23 Jan 1863 2- Anna Cunninghame Graham b. 18 Mar 1802, d. 26 Mar 1886 3- Douglas Cunninghame Graham b. 12 Apr 1805, d. 1856 4- Charlotte Maria Cunninghame Graham b. 3 Jan 1809

He married, secondly, Janet Hunter on 12 December 1816 at Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland.

He died in November 1845 at age 70 at London, England.4,2 He was also known as William Cunningham Bontine Cunninghame Graham.2 He was a yachtsman.5 He lived at Gartmore, Perthshire, ScotlandG.1 Children of William Cunningham Cunninghame Graham, 7th of Gartmore and 16th of Ardoch and Anne Dickson
